24/12/2006
TIRANA, Albania -- The Finance Ministry announced on Friday (December 22nd) that the government seized real estate assets belonging to Saudi businessman Yasin al-Qadi, a suspected aide of al-Qaeda terrorist network leader Osama bin Laden.
According to the statement, the government confiscated five properties, including a house, four bars and shops and over 2 hectares of land in the Tirana region.
Al-Qadi, who fled Albania a few years ago, is on UN and US blacklists of suspected terrorists.
(Focus, Koha jone - 24/12/06;
Albanian News, B92 - 23/12/06)
